        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 8:13PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Powder River Rest Area, which is 34 miles southeast of
Buffalo, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central
Johnson County.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 88 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
